# Artifact Description

## Paper

CATS: Context-Adaptable Tag Signatures for Anonymous Credentials from Lattices

## Artifact Scope

This artifact supports the implementation and performance evaluation in
Section X of the paper. It includes:

1. CATS signing and adaptation procedures.
2. Credential issuance and showing benchmarks.
3. Communication-size accounting scripts.
4. Parameter files for the evaluated 128-bit security profile.
5. Scripts for reproducing Tables X and Y.

## Claims Supported

This artifact supports the following claims:

- CATS reduces median credential issuance time by 34.7% compared with Argo24
  under the controlled benchmark setting.
- CATS reduces median credential showing time by 31.6%.
- CATS achieves sub-240 ms ordinary showing with 72 KB presentation proofs.

## Claims Not Supported

This artifact does not claim to reproduce independent implementations of
Jeudy23, Bootle23, or Chath26. These works are used for functionality and
security positioning only.

